  id: Extensor_digitorum_digitalis_communis_muscle.L
  partName: Extensor digitorum digitalis communis muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left extensor digitorum communis muscle is positioned along the cranial forearm
    of the canine forelimb and functions primarily to extend the digits and carpal
    joint. Originating from the lateral epicondyle of the humerus, it travels distally
    to insert onto the phalanges of multiple digits.
  - This muscle enables coordinated extension of the toes during locomotion, improving
    paw placement and stride efficiency. It also contributes to forelimb stability
    and balance during weight-bearing activities. Proper function is essential for
    smooth gait mechanics and precise limb control.
